<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Error-Code on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/error-code/</link><description>Recent content in Error-Code on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/error-code/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ Boost.Asio - async operation error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/boost-asio-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/boost-asio-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="boostasio---async-operation-error"&gt;Boost.Asio - async operation error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Boost.Asio errors occur during asynchronous operations like socket connect, read, write, or timer operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Connection refused
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;tcp&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;socket socket(io_context);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket.async_connect(endpoint, [](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ECONNREFUSED
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Operation cancelled
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;steady_timer timer(io_context);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;timer.async_wait([](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;operation_aborted) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// timer was cancelled
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: End of file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket.async_read(buffer, [](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; ec, size_t n) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;eof) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// connection closed
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-error-code-in-handlers"&gt;Fix 1: Check error code in handlers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket.async_connect(endpoint, [](&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Connect failed: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; ec.message() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// success
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-error_code-overloads"&gt;Fix 2: Use error_code overloads&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code ec;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;socket.connect(endpoint, ec);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; ec.message() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-handle-specific-errors"&gt;Fix 3: Handle specific errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;connection_refused) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// server not running
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;eof) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// connection closed by peer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; boost&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;asio&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;timed_out) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// operation timed out
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/boost-beast-error/"&gt;Boost.Beast - HTTP error&lt;/a&gt; — HTTP errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-generic/"&gt;std::system_error&lt;/a&gt; — system errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/connection-refused-c/"&gt;C: Connection refused&lt;/a&gt; — ECONNREFUSED.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::filesystem::filesystem_error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/filesystem-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/filesystem-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdfilesystemfilesystem_error"&gt;std::filesystem::filesystem_error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::filesystem::filesystem_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a filesystem operation fails. The error includes the path and error code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: File not found
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;path p &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/nonexistent/file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;file_size(p); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Permission denied
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;remove(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/root/protected.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Path too long
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;string long_path(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;10000&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;a&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;create_directories(long_path); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-error_code-overload"&gt;Fix 1: Use error_code overload&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code ec;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;auto&lt;/span&gt; size &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;file_size(p, ec);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; ec.message() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-existence-first"&gt;Fix 2: Check existence first&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;exists(p)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;remove(p);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-catch-and-handle"&gt;Fix 3: Catch and handle&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;copy_file(src, dst);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem_error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.what() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Path: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.path1() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/filesystem-error/"&gt;std::filesystem::filesystem_error (detailed)&lt;/a&gt; — detailed analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-such-file/"&gt;C: No such file&lt;/a&gt; — ENOENT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/permission-denied-file/"&gt;C: Permission denied&lt;/a&gt; — EACCES.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::system_error - generic category</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-generic/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-generic/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdsystem_error---generic-category"&gt;std::system_error - generic category&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; with the generic category wraps POSIX &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; values. It provides structured error handling for system calls.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: File open failure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;ifstream file(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/nonexistent&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// sets failbit
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Socket error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; sock &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; socket(AF_INET, SOCK_STREAM, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Various system call failures
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Thread creation failure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;thread&lt;/span&gt; t([]{}); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may throw system_error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-use-error_code"&gt;Fix 1: Use error_code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code ec;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;filesystem&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;file_size(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, ec);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;errc&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;no_such_file_or_directory) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;File not found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-catch-and-inspect"&gt;Fix 2: Catch and inspect&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;thread&lt;/span&gt; t([]{ &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* work */&lt;/span&gt; });
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; t.detach();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system_error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Error: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.what() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Code: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.code().value() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-strerror-for-message"&gt;Fix 3: Use strerror for message&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// system call
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system_error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; strerror(e.code().value()) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-system/"&gt;std::system_error - system category&lt;/a&gt; — Windows errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/filesystem-error/"&gt;std::filesystem_error&lt;/a&gt; — filesystem errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/future-error/"&gt;std::future_error&lt;/a&gt; — future/promise errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::system_error - system category</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-system/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-system/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="stdsystem_error---system-category"&gt;std::system_error - system category&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; with the system category wraps platform-specific error codes (Windows error codes on Windows, errno on POSIX).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Windows API failure
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;HANDLE h &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; CreateFile(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, ...); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Winsock error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;WSAStartup(MAKEWORD(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;), &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;wsaData); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may fail
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: POSIX errno
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code ec(errno, std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system_category());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-error-code"&gt;Fix 1: Check error code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// system call
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system_error&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (e.code().category() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;system_category()) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;System error: &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; e.code().value() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-platform-specific-handling"&gt;Fix 2: Use platform-specific handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#ifdef _WIN32
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;DWORD err &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; GetLastError();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Handle Windows error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#else
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; err &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; errno;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Handle POSIX error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#endif
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-stderror_code"&gt;Fix 3: Use std::error_code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-cpp" data-lang="cpp"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;error_code ec;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ... operation that sets ec ...
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (ec) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;cerr &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; ec.message() &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; std&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;::&lt;/span&gt;endl;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-generic/"&gt;std::system_error - generic&lt;/a&gt; — generic errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/filesystem-error/"&gt;std::filesystem_error&lt;/a&gt; — filesystem errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/ios-base-failure/"&gt;std::ios_base::failure&lt;/a&gt; — stream errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Handling Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdsystem_error--system-error-code-handling-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Handling Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a function that uses &lt;code&gt;std::error_code&lt;/code&gt; encounters a failure. It wraps an error code with a human-readable message and category. Many standard library functions — including &lt;code&gt;std::thread&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;std::mutex&lt;/code&gt;, and filesystem operations — throw &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; on failure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdsystem_error-occurs"&gt;Why std::system_error Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include thread creation failures from resource limits, mutex locking failures from deadlock detection, file I/O errors like permission denied or file not found, network socket errors, and failed system calls.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Exception Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/system-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdsystem_error--system-error-code-exception-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Exception Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a function that uses &lt;code&gt;std::error_code&lt;/code&gt; encounters a failure. It wraps an error code with a human-readable message and category, making it the standard way to handle OS-level and library-level errors in C++. Many standard library functions (e.g., &lt;code&gt;std::thread&lt;/code&gt; constructor, &lt;code&gt;std::mutex::lock&lt;/code&gt;, filesystem operations) throw &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; on failure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdsystem_error-occurs"&gt;Why std::system_error Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include OS system call failures (file I/O, networking), thread creation failures (resource limits), mutex locking failures (deadlock detection), failed file operations (permission denied, file not found), and network socket errors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Exception Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/systemerror/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/systemerror/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdsystem_error--system-error-code-exception-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::system_error — System Error Code Exception Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; is thrown when a function that uses &lt;code&gt;std::error_code&lt;/code&gt; encounters a failure. It wraps an error code with a human-readable message and category, making it the standard way to handle OS-level and library-level errors in C++. Many standard library functions (e.g., &lt;code&gt;std::thread&lt;/code&gt; constructor, &lt;code&gt;std::mutex::lock&lt;/code&gt;, filesystem operations) throw &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; on failure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-stdsystem_error-occurs"&gt;Why std::system_error Occurs&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include OS system call failures (file I/O, networking), thread creation failures (resource limits), mutex locking failures (deadlock detection), failed file operations (permission denied, file not found), and network socket errors.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>